  <h2>Installation Tips</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Main panel access:</strong> For CT clamps on the mains, you'll likely need an electrician.</li>
    <li><strong>Wi-Fi strength:</strong> Ensure good signal at your electrical panel location.</li>
    <li><strong>Labeling:</strong> Document which CT goes to which circuit for accurate readings.</li>
    <li><strong>Calibration:</strong> Some monitors allow fine-tuning for maximum accuracy.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>FAQ</h2>

  <h3>Will I need an electrician?</h3>
  <p>
    For main panel CT clamps: usually yes, especially if you need to access the inside of your breaker panel. For smart plugs monitoring individual devices: no electrician needed.
  </p>

  <h3>How accurate are these monitors?</h3>
  <p>
    Quality monitors are typically 1-2% accurate for energy totals. Real-time power readings may vary more but are sufficient for optimization decisions.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I monitor individual circuits?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, many systems support multiple CT clamps. You can monitor your HVAC, EV charger, hot water heater, and other major loads separately.
  </p>
